-- Turkey's Akbank beats forecasts with 893 mln lira Q2 net profit
-- By Ebru Tuncay
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 10:50AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, July 23 (Reuters) - Turkish lender Akbank said on Wednesday its net profit dropped to 893 million lira ($427 million) in the second quarter, but it beat the 763 million lira forecast in a Reuters poll of analysts.

The result compared with a net profit of 914 million in the second quarter a year ago.